---

## **Frontend Folder Structure**

```
frontend/
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ src/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ components/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ pages/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ __tests__/          â† create test folder
â”‚   â”‚    â”œâ”€â”€ Post.test.tsx
â”‚   â”‚    â”œâ”€â”€ NewsForm.test.tsx
â”‚   â”‚    â””â”€â”€ EnhancedFilter.test.tsx
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ jest.config.js
â””â”€â”€ package.json
```

---

## **Frontend installation**

Inside frontend folder:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install --save-dev jest @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom @testing-library/user-event ts-jest @types/jest
```

---

## **Frontend Jest config**

`frontend/jest.config.js`

```js
export default {
  testEnvironment: "jsdom",
  setupFilesAfterEnv: ["@testing-library/jest-dom"],
  transform: {
    "^.+\\.(ts|tsx)$": "ts-jest",
  },
};
```

---

## **Frontend example test**

`frontend/src/__tests__/Post.test.tsx`

```tsx
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import Posts from "../components/Post";

test("renders loading state", () => {
  render(<Posts />);
  expect(screen.getByText(/Loading content/i)).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

